parm:
  pivotal: No
  name: KeyLongPressDelayMode
  type: list
  list:
    - code: 0
      mx: "6.0"
      name: Do not change
      description: A null value (or the absence of this parm from the XML) will cause no change to Enterprise Keyboard settings; any previously selected setting will be retained.
    - code: 1
      name: Specify duration
      mx: "6.0"
      description: Enables specification of the length of time (in ms) that a key must be held before being considered a long press.

---

Controls whether to specify the length of time (in ms) a key must be held down before being considered a long-press (default = 300ms), or to leave the setting unchanged. When "Specify duration" is selected, the long-press delay is set using the "KeyLongPressDelay" parm. 
